g.text: Kim Kitsuragi: "There was little chance he'd be a reliable witness, anyway."
Don't Call Abigail: He waves his hand, as if shooing you away, all the while murmuring something indecipherable.
Don't Call Abigail: His breath smells harsh like a toxic swamp as he whispers to you: "Don't call Abigail. Don't call Abigail!" He then waves his hand, as if shooing you away.
Don't Call Abigail: "Don't call... don't call her..." The drunk man speaks in his sleep. Drool dribbles from the left side of his mouth and down his jacket lapel.
You: "Hey, I'm on an important official investigation, I demand you answer my questions."
Don't Call Abigail: "Abigail?" His voice perks up, then trails into a string of random babbling. "Abigail, where are you?"
Don't Call Abigail: "Don't ya call her, ya hear. Don't call Abigail..."
Don't Call Abigail: He draws out a disgusting snort, then mumbles, waving a finger in your general direction: "Ugh... Abigail... don't ya... fuckin'... call Abigail."
Suggestion: Abigail is his wife or girlfriend. Chances are, she's gone. Calling her wouldn't make it any better or worse.
You: Let him sleep it off. [Leave.]
Don't Call Abigail: There's no waking him from his stupor. His mind is elsewhere.
You: "I'll call whoever I want, don't tell me what to do."
Don't Call Abigail: "Don't call Abigail." The drunk man looks at you with his sad, swollen eyes.
Rhetoric: You're not going to get anything from this guy. He's too drunk.
You: "Who are you? What's your name?"
Don't Call Abigail: His eyes move around erratically, the look in them hazy and unfocused. "Don't call Abigail," he says.
Don't Call Abigail: "Abigail!" He grunts. "Don't... don't call her." He waves a finger in your general direction.
Don't Call Abigail: He glares at you. "Don't ya fuckin' call her, hear me." His voice trembles with every word, becoming ever weaker. "Abigail," he whimpers in the end.
Don't Call Abigail: "Don'... don'..." the man stammers, "don't call..." Slowly, his head nods off to the side and he passes out, tongue dangling from his mouth.
Electrochemistry: Never thought you'd see such a thing in your life, but this guy's a little *too* drunk.
Don't Call Abigail: The dozing man mumbles something inaudible.
Don't Call Abigail: The drunk man starts coughing, a really disgusting hacking cough.
Endurance: He does not sound well at all.
Don't Call Abigail: The man hiccups, then mumbles something unintelligible.
Don't Call Abigail: "Don't... call Abigail..." he whimpers softly, his voice trailing off into nothingness.
Don't Call Abigail: "Don't call Abigail," grumbles an unshaven man with a ruddy nose. He narrows his eyes at you as if in recognition, then turns his head away.
Perception (Smell): The noxious odour emanating from the drunken man is strong and familiar.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant sighs. "You really don't have to... Besides, he will understand you anyway."
Don't Call Abigail: "Abigail... oh, Abigail..." He mutters while trying to brush something off his extremely dirty trousers. His movements are slow and awkward.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right, you might have found the one person who doesn't know you are the law, given how drunk he is."
You: "Have you seen any women around here lately?"
You: "Tell me about your friends." (Point to the others.)
You: "Where am I? What is this place?"
Don't Call Abigail: He snorts and beckons you to lean in closer.
Kim Kitsuragi: "There's no use in yelling at drunks," the lieutenant interjects. "He's barely holding it together."
